Class MessageParsingException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class MessageParsingException
extends AbstractMessageException
    Indicates that a problem was detected during the parsing of a FIX message from raw bytes.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MessageParsingException

        public MessageParsingException(int code,
                               IFIXMessage fixMessage,
                               String message,
                               int msgSeqNum,
                               String msgType,
                               int tagID,
                               BytesSegment rawMessage)
        This constructor allows you to associate a number of extra FIX message values with the exception.

        These extra values are those commonly used in the FIX Session level Reject message.

        Parameters:
        code - Indicates the cause of the message parsing exception.
        fixMessage - FIX message which cause the message parsing exception.
        message - Any text associated with the exception.
        msgSeqNum - Message sequence number of related message - null if unknown.
        msgType - Message type of related message - null if unknown.
        tagID - Tag number of relate message field - 0 if unknown.
        rawMessage - Raw message which was parsed when the exception was raised.
